node.text:
This is truly one of the greatest spontaneous encounters we've seen. We were lucky enough to receive all the raw footage and hear the entire story, a special thanks to @luisorozcoa 🙏
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
When we asked how it all happened he said "As we heard "Orcas" on the radio, adrenaline and excitement started to run through my entire body, I have never seen them before"
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
His words "I was the first one to get in the water, it was freaking cold but I didn't feel anything because of the adrenaline.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
With poor visibility I dived under and was swimming towards nothing until out of nowhere the KING OF THE OCEAN approached me!
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
I dived following one of the orcas when suddenly another one came up blowing bubbles! Never have I seen orcas getting that close to a diver"
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
When we asked him about his experience he said " My mind was almost in shock, It was a one time lifetime experience so there was no room for fear in my mind, I was living the moment full in adrenaline."
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
When the big one came over him and dived right into his face, he could feel the clicks hitting his body.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
He said "Making eye contact with the apex predator of the ocean was the strongest feeling I've ever had, there I did not see a monster but a curious being, just like a child" 😍
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
This spectaculair encounter lasted about 10 minutes
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
©️: @luisorozcoa
With @segeljungs & @bajaadventureco
Via: @savingthewaves

node.title: Face to face with the Apex of the ocean

node.text:
This sad but ultimately uplifting video of a seal rescued from being trapped in fishing net helps to show why over 1 million marine animals — dolphins, fish, sharks, turtles and birds — are killed each year due to plastic debris in the ocean as kind police officers like this aren’t always around to cut these poor animals free from the nets that trap them. There‘s an estimated 100 million tons of plastic in oceans around the world...and nearly half of that plastic waste is fishing nets like this! We are determined to stop this madness before it’s too late, especially considering there’s even more #plasticpollution on land too and spreading awareness about this crisis is the first step so please share this video with your followers and tag people in the comments who need to be made aware of this situation ASAP! It’s we the people who must influence corporations and governments to change their behavior and laws so it’s crucial we WORK TOGETHER ASAP to make this a world that’s safe for humans and animals alike! Will you join us in this fight and help us spread awareness? 
Great video by: Steven Hill
Text via: @savethereef

Via @get.waste.ed 🎥 by @carmelo_isgro 🙌🙏
